                        "id": 14056,
                        "en": "Sulphuric acid",
                        "fr": "Acide sulfurique"
                    },
                    "unitType": {
                        "en": "tonnes",
                        "fr": "tonnes"
                    },
                    "comments": [
                        {
                            "type": {
                                "id": 202,
                                "en": "Substance criteria comment",
                                "fr": "Commentaire sur le statut de déclaration de la substance"
                            },
                            "comment": "Nitric acid and sulphuric acid are used by CRM to clean process equipment.  The resulting acid and water mixture from cleaning is sent to the wastewater treatment plant on-site.  Sulphuric acid is also used in the on-site wastewater treatment plant to lower the pH of the wastewater in a process to remove milk proteins from the wastewater.  After this process, the sulphuric acid in the wastewater is reacted and neutralized before the wastewater is discharged to the municipal sewer system.  Therefore, there are no on-site releases to air, water, or land and off-site transfers of nitric acid and sulphuric acid reported for the facility."
                        }
                    ],
